docs.lead_paragraph: The mood music was upbeat but pragmatic after the first face-to-face meeting in a year between President Biden and his Chinese counterpart, Xi Jinping. headline.main: What the Biden-Xi Talks Accomplished (and Didn't)

docs.snippet: The notifications suggested that many opposition figures could be under “state-sponsored” surveillance, but even Apple said the warning could have been a false alarm.
docs.lead_paragraph: More than a dozen iPhones across India buzzed with the same message earlier this week. Each notification sounded its own little alarm, but was amplified many times over when the targets identified themselves publicly. Most were prominent political opponents of Prime Minister Narendra Modi and his Bharatiya Janata Party.

headline.main: ‘Vague’ iPhone Alert Triggers Serious Accusations of Spying in India
